ObjectStates.LuaScript:
challengeCardsGUID = "df10bd"
endgameChallengeCardsGUID = "5467e3"
GUID_challengeCardsZone = "ac3016"
GUID_discardZone = "28094a"

GUID_CardSlot3 = "e5d237"
GUID_CardSlot2 = "078359"
GUID_CardSlot1 = "50a45d"

--- Callback when 'Custom Tile' object is loaded.
-- @param save_state string: The encoded string containing any save_state (saved) data.
-- @return nil
function onload(save_state)
	self.createButton({	click_function = 'pressed',
   label = 'Create\nDeck',
   function_owner = self,
   position = {0, 0.2, 0},
   rotation = {0, 0, 0},
   scale = {0.6, 0.6, 0.6},
   width = 1500,
   height = 1500,
   font_size = 500  })
end

--- Callback when 'Custom Tile's button is pressed.
-- @param clicked_object: The Object the button is attached to.
-- @param string: Player Color of the player that pressed the button.
-- @return nil
function pressed(clicked_object, player)
  currentPosition = clicked_object.getPosition()
  nextPosition = currentPosition
  nextPosition["y"] = nextPosition["y"] - 0.1
  clicked_object.setPositionSmooth(nextPosition, false, false)

  objChallengeCards = getObjectFromGUID(challengeCardsGUID)
  objEndgameChallengeCards = getObjectFromGUID(endgameChallengeCardsGUID)
  objChallengeCards.randomize()
  objEndgameChallengeCards.randomize()

  takeParams = {
          position = {x=0, y=0, z=0},
          callback_function = function(obj) takeEndGameCardRemove_callback(obj, futureName) end,
          smooth = false,
  }

  while objEndgameChallengeCards.getQuantity() > 6 do
    objEndgameChallengeCards.takeObject(takeParams)
  end

  takeParams = {
          position = {x=0, y=0, z=0},
          callback_function = function(obj) takeEndGameCardAdd_callback(obj, futureName) end,
          smooth = false,
  }

  for i=1,6 do
    objEndgameChallengeCards.takeObject(takeParams)
  end

  clicked_object.destruct()
	objChallengeCards.addContextMenuItem("Deal Cards", onDraw, false)
end

--- Callback when object is removed from deck and "fully exists" when we want to delete it
-- @param object_spawned: The Object created
-- @param name: Name of object
-- @return nil
function takeEndGameCardRemove_callback(object_spawned, name)
  object_spawned.destruct()
end

--- Callback when object is removed from deck and "fully exists" and we want to add it to challenge deck
-- @param object_spawned: The Object created
-- @param name: Name of object
-- @return nil
function takeEndGameCardAdd_callback(object_spawned, name)
  objChallengeCards = getObjectFromGUID(challengeCardsGUID)
  objChallengeCards.putObject(object_spawned)
end

--- Callback when context menu "Deal Cards" is selected. Deals cards to slots.
-- @param player: Color of the player who clicked menu item
-- @return nil
function onDraw(player)
  objChallengeCards = getObjectFromGUID(challengeCardsGUID)
	objZone1 = getObjectFromGUID(GUID_CardSlot1)
	objZone2 = getObjectFromGUID(GUID_CardSlot2)
	objZone3 = getObjectFromGUID(GUID_CardSlot3)

	takeParams = {
          position = {x=0, y=0, z=0},
          smooth = true,
  }

  local Zone1Card = objZone1.getObjects()[1]
	local Zone2Card = objZone2.getObjects()[1]
	local Zone3Card = objZone3.getObjects()[1]
	local FutureZone1Card = nil
	local FutureZone2Card = nil
	local FutureZone3Card = nil


	-- If Zone1 has no cards, grab Zone2, Zone3, or nDeck
	if (Zone1Card == nil) then
		if (Zone2Card ~= nil) then
			FutureZone1Card = Zone2Card
			Zone2Card = nil
		else
			if (Zone3Card ~= nil) then
				FutureZone1Card = Zone3Card
				Zone3Card = nil
			else
				FutureZone1Card = getCardFromDeck()
			end
		end
	end

	-- If Zone2 has no cards, grab Zone3 or Deck
	if (Zone2Card == nil) then
		if (Zone3Card ~= nil) then
			FutureZone2Card = Zone3Card
			Zone3Card = nil
		else
			FutureZone2Card = getCardFromDeck()
		end
	end

	-- If Zone1 has no cards, grab Deck
	if (Zone3Card == nil) then
		FutureZone3Card = getCardFromDeck()
	end

	-- Move all the Cards
	if (FutureZone1Card ~= nil) then
		FutureZone1Card.setPositionSmooth(objZone1.getPosition(), false, true)
    FutureZone1Card.addContextMenuItem("Discard and Deal", discardCard, false)
	end
	if (FutureZone2Card ~= nil) then
		FutureZone2Card.setPositionSmooth(objZone2.getPosition(), false, true)
  end
	if (FutureZone3Card ~= nil) then
		FutureZone3Card.setPositionSmooth(objZone3.getPosition(), false, true)
	end

	objChallengeCards.removeFromPlayerSelection(player)
end

--- Function to handle getting cards from both deck and single cards. Adds
--  context menu to single card so it acts like a deck. Removes it when dealt.
-- @return nil
function getCardFromDeck()
  deckZone = getObjectFromGUID(GUID_challengeCardsZone)
  deck = deckZone.getObjects()[1]
  drawnCard = nil

  if ( deck ~= nil ) then
    if ( deck.tag == "Deck") then
      takeParams = {
              position = {x=0, y=0, z=0},
              smooth = true,
      }
      if (deck.getQuantity() == 2) then
        -- There will be only one card left, deck destroyed
        drawnCard = deck.takeObject(takeParams)
        remainingCard = deck.takeObject(takeParams)
        remainingCard.addContextMenuItem("Draw Cards", onDraw, false)
        remainingCard.setPositionSmooth(deckZone.getPosition(), false, true)
      else
        drawnCard = deck.takeObject(takeParams)
      end

    else
      drawnCard = deck
      deck.clearContextMenu()
    end
  end
  return drawnCard
end

--- Flips card, moves it discord zone, and delays 40ms.
-- @param player: Color of the player who clicked menu item
-- @return nil
function discardCard(player)
  objZone1 = getObjectFromGUID(GUID_CardSlot1)
  discardZone = getObjectFromGUID(GUID_discardZone)

	local Zone1Card = objZone1.getObjects()[1]
  if (Zone1Card ~= nil ) then
    if (not Zone1Card.is_face_down) then
      Zone1Card.flip()
    end
    Zone1Card.setPositionSmooth(discardZone.getPosition(), false, true)
		Zone1Card.removeFromPlayerSelection(player)
  end

  Wait.frames(onDraw, 40)
end

--[[ Lua code. See documentation: https://api.tabletopsimulator.com/ --]]
GUID_GreenDugout   = "58df91"
GUID_GreenDiceZone = "fd10fe"
GUID_GreenCardZone = "3b47d7"

GUID_RedDugout    = "365825"
GUID_RedDiceZone  = "15a9c3"
GUID_RedCardZone  = "378000"

GUID_BigScoreZone = "7d4b35"
GUID_ZeroScoreZone= "c24486"

GUID_ChaosBag     = "babfb2"
GUID_DarkElvesBag = "0043cf"
GUID_DwarfBag     = "7385c2"
GUID_ElvenBag     = "a79f0e"
GUID_GoblinBag    = "4ba978"
GUID_HalflingsBag = "da70f7"
GUID_HumanBag     = "1b15fb"
GUID_LizardmenBag = "1352b6"
--GUID_OgreBag      = "1e3fa5"
GUID_OrcBag       = "f4793a"
GUID_NurgleBag    = "a9cfc6"
GUID_SkavenBag    = "e058fe"
GUID_UndeadBag    = "3a1403"
GUID_WoodElvesBag = "e72185"

BagGUIDs = {GUID_GoblinBag, GUID_ChaosBag, GUID_OrcBag, GUID_SkavenBag, GUID_DwarfBag,
            GUID_ElvenBag, GUID_DarkElvesBag, GUID_HumanBag, GUID_HalflingsBag,
            GUID_UndeadBag, GUID_WoodElvesBag, GUID_LizardmenBag, GUID_NurgleBag}

GUID_CardSlot1    = "50a45d"

--- The onLoad event is called after the game save finishes loading.
function onLoad()
  for i, guid in ipairs(BagGUIDs) do
    local bag = getObjectFromGUID(guid)
    bag.addContextMenuItem("Grab Contents", function (...) emptyBag(bag.guid, ...) end)
  end
end

function onObjectLeaveScriptingZone(zone, leave_object)
	if (zone.getGUID() == GUID_CardSlot1) then
    leave_object.clearContextMenu()
	end
end

function emptyBag(obj_guid, player)
  local obj = getObjectFromGUID(obj_guid)
  local zModDugout = -1.4
  local zModDice = 1.8

  if (obj.tag == "Bag") then
    targetSmallScoreZone = getObjectFromGUID(GUID_ZeroScoreZone)
    targetBigScoreZone   = getObjectFromGUID(GUID_BigScoreZone)
    if (player == "Red") then
      targetCardZone     = getObjectFromGUID(GUID_RedCardZone)
      targetDiceZone     = getObjectFromGUID(GUID_RedDiceZone)
      targetDugoutZone   = getObjectFromGUID(GUID_RedDugout)
    elseif (player == "Green") then
      targetCardZone     = getObjectFromGUID(GUID_GreenCardZone)
      targetDiceZone     = getObjectFromGUID(GUID_GreenDiceZone)
      targetDugoutZone   = getObjectFromGUID(GUID_GreenDugout)
    else
      return
    end

    local diceTargetLoc   = targetDiceZone.getPosition()
    diceTargetLoc.y = diceTargetLoc.y - 3

    local cardTargetLoc   = targetCardZone.getPosition()

    local dugoutTargetLoc = targetDugoutZone.getPosition()
    dugoutTargetLoc.x = dugoutTargetLoc.x + (targetDugoutZone.getScale().x / 2) - 1.0
    dugoutTargetLoc.y = dugoutTargetLoc.y
    dugoutTargetLoc.z = dugoutTargetLoc.z + (targetDugoutZone.getScale().z / 2) - 0.5

    local smallScoreLoc = targetSmallScoreZone.getPosition()
    smallScoreLoc.x = smallScoreLoc.x - 0.3
    smallScoreLoc.z = smallScoreLoc.z - 0.3
    local bigScoreLoc   = targetBigScoreZone.getPosition()

    repeat
      takeParams = {
              position = {x=0, y=0, z=0},
              smooth = true,
      }
      local item = obj.takeObject(takeParams)
      if (item.tag == "Dice") then
        diceTargetLoc.z = diceTargetLoc.z + (zModDice / 2)
        item.setPosition(diceTargetLoc, false, true)
        diceTargetLoc.x = diceTargetLoc.x + item.getBoundsNormalized().size.x - 1.2
        zModDice = -zModDice

      elseif (item.tag == "Tile" and item.GetName() == "Score Marker") then
        if (player == "Red") then
          smallScoreLoc.z = smallScoreLoc.z + 0.4
          smallScoreLoc.x = smallScoreLoc.x + 0.4
        end
        item.setPosition(smallScoreLoc, false, true)

      elseif (item.tag == "Tile" and item.GetName() == "Big Score Marker") then
        if (player == "Red") then
          bigScoreLoc.z = bigScoreLoc.z + 1.0
          bigScoreLoc.x = bigScoreLoc.x + 1.0
        end
        item.setPosition(bigScoreLoc, false, true)

      elseif (item.tag == "Tileset") then
        dugoutTargetLoc.z = dugoutTargetLoc.z + (zModDugout / 2)
        item.setPosition(dugoutTargetLoc, false, true)
        dugoutTargetLoc.x = dugoutTargetLoc.x + item.getBoundsNormalized().size.x - 1.3
        zModDugout = -zModDugout

      elseif (item.tag == "Deck" or item.tag == "Card") then
        --print("Deck: " .. targetDiceZone.getPosition())
        item.setPositionSmooth(targetCardZone.getPosition(), false, true)
        if (player == "Red") then
          item.setRotation(Vector(0,180,0))
        end
      end
      Wait.frames(function() noFunc() end, 100)
    until obj.getQuantity() == 0
  end
end

function noFunc()
end
